\mt1 Malaki
\mt2 (Malachi)
\is1 Introduction
\ip This document records some of God's messages that were given to the prophet Malaki (more accurately вҖҳMalКјДҒkД«вҖҷ, although traditionally spelt as вҖҳMalachiвҖҷ) to pass on to the Israeli people. It was written around 500 years before Yeshua/Jesus (B.C.) once the replacement temple was finished in Yerushalem (Jerusalem). The main purpose of the messages is to encourage the priests and the people to turn back to God and obey him from their hearts. It's apparent that many of them were no longer obeying and worshipping God. The priests and the people were short-changing God by offering second-class animals for the sacrifices and none of them were following God's desires. But God intervened in order to judge and restore his people, and he will send a teacher to precede him to prepare the path and to restore his agreement.
\iot Main components of this account
\io1 The sins of the Israelis \ior 1:1вҖ“2:16\ior*
\io1 God's judgement and mercy \ior 2:17вҖ“4:6\ior*
\rem This is still a very early look into the unfinished text of the Open English Translation of the Bible. Please double-check the text in advance before using in public.
\ie
\c 1
\p
\v 1 This is a messageВҰ380162 that YahwehВҰ380164 gave to Malaki for the Israelis:
\s1 Yahweh's love for the Israelis
\rem /s1 The Lord's Love for Israel; Jacob Loved, Esau Hated; Religious decline and hope of recovery; Israel Preferred to Edom; The Lord's Love for Israel
\p
\v 2 вҖңI have loved you all,вҖқ says Yahweh, \add вүҲbutВҰ380175\add* you say, вҖңHow have you \add shown your\add* love for us?вҖқ
\p вҖңWasn't EsawВҰ380181 Yacob'sВҰ380182 brotherВҰ380180?вҖқ declares Yahweh. вҖңYet I'veВҰ380171 loved Yacob\x + \xo 1:2-3: \xt Rom 9:13.\x*
\v 3 and \add вүҲrejected\add* Esaw. I'veВҰ380195 turnedВҰ380195 the hills \add where Esaw lived\add* into a wastelandВҰ380199 and \add given\add* his inheritanceВҰ380202 to the wild jackalsВҰ380203.вҖқ
\p
\v 4 If \add Esaw's descendants in\add* EdomВҰ380209 say, вҖңWe've \add вүҲbeen crushed\add*, but we'll returnВҰ380211 and \add вүҲrebuildВҰ380212 what was destroyed\add*,вҖқ then army-commanderВҰ380217 Yahweh will say, вҖңThey might buildВҰ380219, but I will tear down. Others will call them вҖҳThe country of wickednessВҰ380225вҖҷ and вҖҳThe peopleВҰ380226 who Yahweh is forever angry with.вҖҷ
\p
\v 5 Your own eyesВҰ380235 will seeВҰ380236 it, andВҰ380237 you'll sayВҰ380238, вҖҳYahwehВҰ380240 is greatВҰ380239 even outside Yisrael'sВҰ380243 bordersВҰ380242.вҖҷ вҖқ
\s1 Second-class sacrifices
\rem /s1 The Lord Reprimands the Priests; Unworthy Sacrifices; Blemished Sacrifices; Corruption of the Priesthood
\p
\v 6 вҖңA son honours his father, and a servantВҰ380248 \add вүЎhonours\add* his master, \add вүҲso\add* if I'm a father, where is my honour? If I am a master, where is my respectВҰ380261?вҖқ says army-commanderВҰ380265 YahwehВҰ380264 to all you priestsВҰ380267 who despise my name.
\p вҖңButВҰ380248 you say, вҖҳHow have we despised your name?вҖҷ
\v 7 By offering polluted food onВҰ380284 my altarВҰ380280. ButВҰ380283 you sayВҰ380283, вҖҳHow have we polluted you?вҖҷ By sayingВҰ380286 that Yahweh'sВҰ380288 tableВҰ380287 can \add just\add* be disrespected.
\v 8 Don'tВҰ380297 you think it's wrong when you sacrificeВҰ380296 blindВҰ380295 animals? Isn't it evil when you offerВҰ380294 lame or sick \add вүЎanimals\add*? Try presentingВҰ380305 them to yourВҰ380314 governorВҰ380307! Will he welcome you or wouldВҰ380313 he \add вүҲbe offended\add*?вҖқ saysВҰ380315 army-commanderВҰ380317 YahwehВҰ380316.\x + \xo 1:8: \xt Deu 15:21.\x*
\p
\v 9 \add вүҲSoВҰ380319 now\add* bring you requests to GodВҰ380325 andВҰ380319 \add вүҲhope to be showered by his grace\add*. \add Ha,\add* army-commanderВҰ380336 YahwehВҰ380335 \add вүҲasks how he could treat you all favourablyВҰ380326 when you're bringing second-class offerings\add*?
\p
\v 10 вҖңYeah, if only thereВҰ380349 was one \add >person\add* amongВҰ380341 you who would shut the temple gates so that you all couldn't \add just continue\add* to lightВҰ380346 worthless fires onВҰ380341 my altarВҰ380347. I get no pleasureВҰ380352 from you all,вҖқ saysВҰ380354 army-commanderВҰ380356 YahwehВҰ380355, вҖңand I won'tВҰ380344 acceptВҰ380360 any offeringВҰ380357 \add вүҲthat you all bring me\add*.
\v 11 People in other countries from the east \add all the way\add* to the west will honour me, and incenseВҰ380376 and genuine sacrifices will be offeredВҰ380379 to me, becauseВҰ380381 my reputationВҰ380371 in those countries will be praised,вҖқ saysВҰ380386 army-commanderВҰ380388 YahwehВҰ380387.
\v 12 вҖңButВҰ380392 you all are dishonouring \add @my name\add* when you sayВҰ380393 that the master'sВҰ380395 tableВҰ380394 is polluted, andВҰ380390 that its fruitВҰ380398, its food, can be treated withВҰ380393 contempt.
\v 13 You all also say, вҖҳHow tiresome this is,вҖҷ andВҰ380402 you snort at it,вҖқ says army-commanderВҰ380409 Yahweh. вҖңYou all bring \add animals\add* for your offeringВҰ380421 that were killed by a wild animal or is lame or sick. Should I acceptВҰ380422 those from you?вҖқ says Yahweh.
\v 14 вҖңMay the cheats be cursedВҰ380429 who have maleВҰ380433 animals inВҰ380432 their flocksВҰ380432 and vow to give them, butВҰ380429 instead sacrificesВҰ380435 a second-class animal to the masterВҰ380437! Yes, I'm a powerful kingВҰ380439,вҖқ saysВҰ380442 army-commanderВҰ380444 YahwehВҰ380443, вҖңand my nameВҰ380445 will be carefully respected among the nationsВҰ380447.вҖқ
\c 2
\s1 A warning for the priests
\rem /s1 Admonition for the Priests; A Warning for the Priests
\p
\v 1 NowВҰ380453 you priestsВҰ380453, this commandВҰ380451 is for all of you:
\v 2 Army-commanderВҰ380471 YahwehВҰ380470 saysВҰ380469, вҖңIf you all won't listenВҰ380458 and won't \add вүҲdecide in your minds\add* to honourВҰ380467 to my \add вүҲreputationВҰ380468\add*, then I'll sendВҰ380472 a curse onВҰ380473 you allвҖ”\add вүҲin fact\add* I'll curse your blessingsВҰ380480. Indeed, I'veВҰ380482 \add already\add* cursed them, becauseВҰ380483 you all are not \add вүҲinternalising\add* \add <my instructions\add*.
\v 3 Listen, I'm aboutВҰ380491 to rebukeВҰ380491 your descendants, and I'llВҰ380496 spreadВҰ380496 the offal from your festivalsВҰ380502 on your facesВҰ380500, and you all will be takenВҰ380503 away with it.
\v 4 That's so you'll all knowВҰ380507 that it's me who sentВҰ380509 this commandВҰ380512 to you: so that my agreementВҰ380515 with the Levites can continue,вҖқ saysВҰ380519 army-commanderВҰ380521 YahwehВҰ380520.\x + \xo 2:4: \xt Num 3:11-13.\x*
\p
\v 5 вҖңMy agreement with \add @your ancestor Levi\add* was \add to give\add* lifeВҰ380527 and peaceВҰ380528, and I gaveВҰ380529 them to \add #them\add*. It was an agreement \add вүҲbased on respect\add*, and \add #they\add* respected me and \add вүҲhonoured\add* my nameВҰ380535.\x + \xo 2:5: \xt Num 25:12.\x*
\v 6 \add вүҲThey taught the people what was right and trueвҖ”they didn'tВҰ380544 tell lies\add*. \add #They\add* \add вүҲworked for me peacefullyВҰ380548 and loyally\add*, and they \add вүҲencouraged many people to stop disobeying\add*.
\v 7 \add вүҲYes,\add* priestsВҰ380559 should pass on knowledgeВҰ380562 andВҰ380563 peopleВҰ380564 should look to \add #them\add* \add вүҲfor good teaching\add*, becauseВҰ380566 theyВҰ380560 are army-commanderВҰ380570 Yahweh'sВҰ380568 messengersВҰ380567.
\p
\v 8 ButВҰ380573 you all have turnedВҰ380574 away from \add that\add* pathВҰ380577 andВҰ380573 have causedВҰ380578 many \add >people\add* to stumbleВҰ380578 \add вүҲbecause of what you've taught\add*вҖ”you all have corruptedВҰ380581 the agreementВҰ380582 withВҰ380580 LeviВҰ380583,вҖқ saysВҰ380584 army-commanderВҰ380586 YahwehВҰ380585.
\v 9 вҖңSoВҰ380588 that's why I'veВҰ380591 caused you all to be despisedВҰ380593 by all the peopleВҰ380597 andВҰ380588 humiliatedвҖ”becauseВҰ380598 you all haven't \add вүҲfollowed me\add*, butВҰ380588 rather you've been biased inВҰ380607 mattersВҰ380598 of the law.вҖқ
\s1 The people have been unfaithful
\rem /s1 A Call to Faithfulness; The Covenant Profaned by Judah; Judah Unfaithful; The People's Unfaithfulness to God
\p
\v 10 Don'tВҰ380610 we all have one fatherВҰ380611? Didn't the one GodВҰ380615 createВҰ380617 us all? \add So\add* why doВҰ380619 we cheat each other, thus disrespecting the agreementВҰ380623 withВҰ380621 ourВҰ380613 ancestorsВҰ380624?
\v 11 \add Our nation of\add* YehudahВҰ380627 \add (Judah)\add* has been unfaithful \add to Yahweh\add* and doneВҰ380629 detestable things in YisraelВҰ380630 and in YerushalemВҰ380631. \add вүҲOur men\add* have defiled the temple thatВҰ380638 Yahweh lovesВҰ380639 by \add вүҲmarrying foreignВҰ380644 women who worship pagan gods\add*.
\v 12 May Yahweh, the one who is awake and the one who answersВҰ380652, banish the \add #men\add* who do this from Yisrael, even if \add #they\add* are bringingВҰ380655 an offeringВҰ380656 to army-commanderВҰ380658 Yahweh.
\p
\v 13 SecondlyВҰ380666, you coverВҰ380664 Yahweh'sВҰ380669 altarВҰ380668 with tears from all your weepingВҰ380670 and groaningВҰ380671 becauseВҰ380672 he stillВҰ380673 ignores your offeringsВҰ380677 and won'tВҰ380672 acceptВҰ380678 what you all bring to him.
\v 14 \add вүҲSoВҰ380682\add* you \add вүҲask\add*, вҖңWhy not?вҖқ \add Well,\add* it's becauseВҰ380687 YahwehВҰ380689 can testifyВҰ380690 that you'veВҰ380698 been unfaithful to the wife that you \add вүҲmarried\add* when you were young, even though she was your companionВҰ380701, andВҰ380682 despite your vows.
\v 15 Didn't \add @Yahweh\add* make \add you and your wife\add* one and give you some of his spirit because he wanted godly children \add to come from your marriage\add*? \add вүҲSoВҰ380705\add* guardВҰ380717 yourselves inВҰ380718 your spirit, and don'tВҰ380705 be unfaithful to the \add вүҲwoman you married when you were young\add*.
\p
\v 16 вҖңIndeed, I hate divorce,вҖқ says Yahweh, the godВҰ380731 of YisraelВҰ380732, вҖңand \add вүҲso-called вҖҳgood peopleвҖҷ who are actually cruel\add*,вҖқ says army-commanderВҰ380740 Yahweh. вҖңSo \add вүҲlisten to your consciences\add* and don'tВҰ380743 be unfaithful.вҖқ
\s1 Judgement day is coming
\rem /s1 The Day of Judgment; The Day of Judgment Is Near
\p
\v 17 You've all wearied Yahweh with yourВҰ380753 wordsВҰ380749, and \add yet\add* you \add вүҲaskВҰ380750\add*, вҖңHow have weВҰ380752 wearied himВҰ380752?вҖқ By sayingВҰ380753, вҖңYahweh is pleased \add even\add* with those who do evilВҰ380757, and he's happy with \add all\add* of them,вҖқ or вҖңWhere is the godВҰ380767 of justiceВҰ380768?вҖқ
\c 3
\rem /s1 The Coming Day of Judgment; The Coming Messenger
\p
\v 1 вҖңListen, I'm about to send my messenger and he'll prepareВҰ380773 the pathВҰ380775 ahead of me. Then the masterВҰ380782 who you're all lookingВҰ380787 forВҰ380787 will suddenlyВҰ380777 come to his templeВҰ380781, \add yes,\add* the messenger who you are all happy aboutвҖ”the party to the agreementВҰ380789вҖ”he'll come,вҖқ says army-commanderВҰ380799 YahwehВҰ380798.\x + \xo 3:1: \xt Mat 11:10; Mrk 1:2; Luk 1:76; 7:27.\x*
\v 2 \add вүҲButВҰ380801 who could survive it when he comes\add*? WhoВҰ380803 can standВҰ380808 when he appearsВҰ380809, becauseВҰ380810 he'll be like the refiner'sВҰ380814 fireВҰ380813 andВҰ380801 like the cleaners' \add powerful\add* soap?\x + \xo 3:2: \xt Yoel 2:11; Rev 6:17.\x*
\v 3 \add @Yahweh\add* will act as a refiner and purifier of silver, and he will purify Levi'sВҰ380827 descendantsВҰ380825 \add the priests\add*вҖ”\add yes,\add* he'll refine \add &you all\add* \add withВҰ380836 fire\add* like goldВҰ380830 and silver, and \add &you'll\add* bringВҰ380834 offeringsВҰ380835 to \add *him\add* that are \add вүҲacceptable\add*.
\v 4 \add After that,\add* the offeringsВҰ380840 of \add the people of\add* Yudah and YerushalemВҰ380842 will be pleasingВҰ380838 to YahwehВҰ380839, as in \add вүҲancient times\add*, and as in previous yearsВҰ380845.
\p
\v 5 This is what army-commanderВҰ380872 YahwehВҰ380871 saysВҰ380870, вҖңAt that time, I'll come to you all to judgeВҰ380850 you. I'll quickly testify against all those who practice sorceryВҰ380855, \add вүЎagainst\add* adulterersВҰ380856, \add вүЎagainst\add* those who \add вүҲlie inВҰ380855 court\add*, \add вүЎagainst\add* those who \add вүҲdon't pay their workers fairly\add*, \add вүЎagainst\add* those who mistreat widowsВҰ380863 and orphansВҰ380864, \add вүЎagainst\add* those who \add вүҲdon't treat the foreigners among you decently\add*, and \add вүЎagainst\add* those who \add вүҲrefuse to honour\add* me.
\s1 Giving a tenth
\rem /s1 The Payment of Tithes; Robbing God; A Call to Repentance
\p
\v 6 вҖңI am YahwehВҰ380876 andВҰ380879 I don'tВҰ380877 changeВҰ380878вҖ”that's the \add only\add* reason why you descendantsВҰ380880 of YacobВҰ380882 haven't been destroyed.
\v 7 Ever sinceВҰ380886 the timeВҰ380886 when your ancestorsВҰ380887 were alive, you all have \add вүҲignored my commands\add* and \add вүҲrefused to obey\add* them. \add Now\add* return to meвҖ”\add if you all do so,\add* I'llВҰ380894 return to you. That's what I, army-commanderВҰ380898 YahwehВҰ380897, sayВҰ380899. ButВҰ380890 you all ask, вҖҳHow can weВҰ380901 return to you?вҖҷ
\rem /s1 Don't rob God
\v 8 Can a human rob GodВҰ380905? \add Yes,\add* you're all robbing me, butВҰ380910 you ask, вҖҳHow are we robbing you?вҖҷ \add By failing to give\add* a tenth plusВҰ380910 offeringsВҰ380914.
\v 9 You'reВҰ380919 all cursedВҰ380916 because you're robbingВҰ380921 meвҖ”the wholeВҰ380923 nationВҰ380922 of you.
\v 10 BringВҰ380925 the full tenth into the temple storeroomВҰ380934, so that there'll be food inВҰ380937 my house \add for the temple workers\add*,вҖқ says army-commanderВҰ380943 YahwehВҰ380942. вҖң\add In fact,\add* you all can test me \add вүҲby doing that and see\add* if I don'tВҰ380946 open the windowsВҰ380950 of heavenВҰ380951 for you all and pour out an \add вүҲoverflowing\add* blessingВҰ380954 for you.\x + \xo 3:10: \xt Lev 27:30; Num 18:21-24; Deu 12:6; 14:22-29; Neh 13:12.\x*
\v 11 I'llВҰ380968 rebukeВҰ380961 the devourerВҰ380963\f + \fr 3:11 \ft This is literally the вҖҳeaterвҖҷ which could refer to some kind of insect (and hence вҖҳ\+em it\+em* won't destroyвҖҷ in the next clause) or it could refer to some spiritual power (then you'd get вҖҳ\+em he\+em* won't destroyвҖҷ).\f* for you all, so that it won't destroyВҰ380966 your crops, and the fruitВҰ380970 off your vines in the countrysideВҰ380977 won't be lost,вҖқ saysВҰ380978 army-commanderВҰ380980 YahwehВҰ380979.
\v 12 вҖңThenВҰ380983 all the other countriesВҰ380986 would say that you've all been blessedВҰ380982, becauseВҰ380987 yourВҰ380984 land \add вүҲwould be prosperous\add*,вҖқ saysВҰ380993 army-commanderВҰ380995 YahwehВҰ380994.
\s1 God promises mercy for some
\rem /s1 The righteous triumphant; God's Promise of Mercy
\p
\v 13 вҖңYour wordsВҰ381000 against me have been harsh,вҖқ saysВҰ381001 YahwehВҰ381002. вҖңButВҰ381003 you all sayВҰ381003, вҖҳWhat have we said among ourselves against you?вҖҷ
\v 14 You've all saidВҰ381009, вҖҳIt's \add вүҲa waste of time\add* serving GodВҰ381012. What did we gain by keeping his requirementsВҰ381018, or by \add вүҲbeing sorrowful\add* in frontВҰ381022 of army-commanderВҰ381024 YahwehВҰ381023?
\v 15 \add вүҲIt seems that arrogantВҰ381029 people are happier\add*. Evil people not only prosper, butВҰ381026 they \add even\add* \add вүҲchallenge GodВҰ381037 yet nothing happens to them\add*.вҖҷ вҖқ
\rem /s1 The Reward of the Faithful; The Lord's Promise of Mercy
\p
\v 16 Then those who \add вүҲstill respected\add* Yahweh spokeВҰ381041 with one another. Yahweh paid attentionВҰ381048 and listenedВҰ381050, and \add вүҲwhile he watched\add*, a book of remembranceВҰ381053 was writtenВҰ381051 about those who respected Yahweh and honoured hisВҰ381054 nameВҰ381058.
\v 17 вҖңThey'll be mine,вҖқ saysВҰ381062 army-commanderВҰ381064 YahwehВҰ381063. вҖңOn the dayВҰ381065 when I \add вүҲassemble\add* my treasured possessionВҰ381069, I \add вүҲwon't punish\add* \add @those people\add*, just like a \add вүҲfather doesn't punish\add* his son who \add вүҲobeys\add* him.
\v 18 ThenВҰ381081 once againВҰ381081 you'll all \add вүҲbe able to seeВҰ381082 the difference\add* between righteousВҰ381084 \add >people\add* and wickedВҰ381085 \add >people\add*вҖ”between \add #those\add* who serveВҰ381091 GodВҰ381088 and \add #those\add* who don'tВҰ381090.
\c 4
\s1 Be ready for future judgement
\rem /s1 The Day of the Lord; The Coming Day of Judgment; The Day of the Lord Is Coming; The Great Day of the Lord
\p
\v 1 вҖң\add вүҲYes,\add* listen, the day that burns like a furnace is coming, when all the arrogant \add >people\add* and all the evildoers will become \add вүҲuseless pieces of dry stalks in a field\add*. The day that is coming will burn them up,вҖқ says army-commander Yahweh, вҖңso \add вүҲthey'll be gone without leaving any\add* roots or branches.
\v 2 But for you who respect my name, the sun of righteousness will rise \add вүҲand bring\add* healing. You'll all go out, jumping around like calves \add let out of their\add* stall,
\v 3 and you'll all trample down the wicked \add >people\add*, because they'll \add just\add* be ashes under the soles of your feet on the day that I act,вҖқ says army-commander Yahweh.
\p
\v 4 вҖң\add вүҲBe sure to obey\add* the law that I \add вүҲgave\add* my servant Mosheh at \add вүҲMt. Sinai\add* for all IsraelвҖ”the statutes and the rulings.
\p
\v 5 Listen, I'll send the prophet Eliyah to you all, \add ahead\add* of the coming of the great \add вүҲbut\add* fearful day of \add *my\add* \add judgement\add*.\x + \xo 4:5: \xt Mat 11:14; 17:10-13; Mrk 9:11-13; Luk 1:17; Yhn 1:21.\x*
\v 6 He'll \add вүҲrestore harmony between fathers and their children\add*, so that I don't \add have to\add* come and strike the earth with complete destruction.вҖқ
